✅ Yes, that’s absolutely correct!

You have successfully created the two folders with the right structure and permissions.

Here’s what your setup means:

/var/www/bbiq/
├── counselorSignature/   ✅ exists
└── usersSignature/       ✅ exists


Both folders belong to user redcrossdewas.

Permissions drwxr-xr-x (755) → good for most web apps.

Path matches exactly what your app expects:

USER_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH=/var/www/bbiq/usersSignature
COUNSELOR_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH=/var/www/bbiq/counselorSignature


💡 Next step (optional but recommended):
If you haven’t already, set these environment variables permanently so your backend always knows these paths — even after a restart.

You can do that by adding to your shell config:

echo 'export USER_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH=/var/www/bbiq/usersSignature' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export COUNSELOR_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH=/var/www/bbiq/counselorSignature' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc


Then verify:

echo $USER_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH
echo $COUNSELOR_SIGNATURE_FOLDER_PATH


